The paper deals with lower bounds for graph problems in the streaming model of computation, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of communication problems and reductions suggests that information theory (cs.IT) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM) may also be relevant sub-categories. Finally, the mention of submodular function minimization and adaptivity suggests that machine learning (cs.LG) may also be a relevant sub-category.
